columns_data: Detection of demanded clearance position after clamp force reduction could not be achieved within plausible time.
During brake release, voltage in operational range

Decrease of clamp force (without setting clearance) takes more than 4.0 seconds
OR setting of clearance takes more than 1.6 sec
OR idle current is lower than low current threshold (OPTIONAL: if necessary in project a project specific evaluation is necessary; e.g. 300 mA) for at least low current detection time (OPTIONAL: if necessary in project a project specific evaluation is necessary; e.g. 100 ms)
OR idle current is is greater than 7.5 A just before clearance is set

columns_data: EPB system actuation aborted due to PBC external reasons. At least one actuator position is unknown.

Actuator State was set to unknown due to one of the following reasons:
1) HostAvailability different from AVAILABILITY_APPLY_RELEASE during actuation.
2) - MotorDriverState doesn't match MotorCommand for longer than 800ms during running actuation (EPBi FSS)
 - MotorDriverState doesn't match MotorCommand for longer than 80ms during running actuation (EPBi brake assembly)

Actuatorstate left resume in final state "Released" or "CompletelyReleased" 
or (after previous actuation in release direction) "ParkApplied" or "HoldApplied".
